    "content_list_drW7jD": {
      "type": "content-list",
      "blocks": {
        "image_P67RpV": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "apply_overlay": false,
            "devices": "mobile_desktop",
            "content_position": "underLeft",
            "subheading": "",
            "title": "<p>Jewellery Can Become Part Of The Story</p>",
            "description": "<p>The jewellery chosen for a wedding often carries meaning far beyond the styling.</p><p>For Shona, that meaning became a gift for her husband. On the morning of their wedding, she surprised him with a necklace featuring a diamond from his late grandmother's tennis bracelet. </p><p>\"She would have loved to be there on our wedding day. It meant she could still be with him, close to his heart.\"</p><p>Little did Shona know, Connor had planned a meaningful surprise of his own.</p><p>On the morning of their wedding, he gifted her our Ember Bracelet - a piece Shona had designed just months earlier - custom set with a single sapphire as her \"something blue.\"</p><p>For Helen, jewellery became a way of creating lasting keepsakes for the youngest members of the bridal party. Each flower girl received a pendant featuring a pink diamond from the very same parcel as the diamonds in Helen's own wedding earrings. The back of every pendant was engraved with a handwritten message in her own handwriting, creating a piece they can treasure for years to come.</p><p>Jewellery has the unique ability to become more than something you wear. When layered with sentiment, it becomes another way of telling your story, carrying the people, memories and milestones you want to hold close long after the celebrations have ended.</p>",
            "description_mobile": "<p>The jewellery chosen for a wedding often carries meaning far beyond the styling.</p><p>For Shona, that meaning became a gift for her husband. On the morning of their wedding, she surprised him with a necklace featuring a diamond from his late grandmother's tennis bracelet. </p><p>\"She would have loved to be there on our wedding day. It meant she could still be with him, close to his heart.\"</p><p>Little did Shona know, Connor had planned a meaningful surprise of his own.</p><p>On the morning of their wedding, he gifted her our Ember Bracelet - a piece Shona had designed just months earlier - custom set with a single sapphire as her \"something blue.\"</p><p>For Helen, jewellery became a way of creating lasting keepsakes for the youngest members of the bridal party. Each flower girl received a pendant featuring a pink diamond from the very same parcel as the diamonds in Helen's own wedding earrings. The back of every pendant was engraved with a handwritten message in her own handwriting, creating a piece they can treasure for years to come.</p><p>Jewellery has the unique ability to become more than something you wear. When layered with sentiment, it becomes another way of telling your story, carrying the people, memories and milestones you want to hold close long after the celebrations have ended.</p>",
            "colour_style": "dark",
