    "content_list_D7Nrpt": {
      "type": "content-list",
      "blocks": {
        "image_M47rxC": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "apply_overlay": false,
            "devices": "mobile_desktop",
            "content_position": "underLeft",
            "subheading": "",
            "title": "<p>Honour The People Who Helped Shape Your Story</p>",
            "description": "<p>A wedding is not only a celebration of two people. It is also a celebration of everyone who helped bring them together.</p><p>For Natalie and Dan, honouring family became one of the most meaningful parts of their ceremony.</p><p>\"We both took a moment to thank our mothers for their guidance, love and support, and ultimately for helping us find our way to one another.\"</p>",
            "description_mobile": "<p>A wedding is not only a celebration of two people. It is also a celebration of everyone who helped bring them together.</p><p>For Natalie and Dan, honouring family became one of the most meaningful parts of their ceremony.</p><p>\"We both took a moment to thank our mothers for their guidance, love and support, and ultimately for helping us find our way to one another.\"</p><p>As jewellery has always held such a significant part of their story, they also chose to include a tradition that felt deeply aligned with what wedding rings represent.</p><p>Their rings were passed throughout the ceremony in a small palm-shaped dish for a traditional <em>ring warming</em>, allowing every guest to hold them briefly and quietly offer a blessing before they exchanged vows.</p><p>\"We wanted our wedding rings to carry not only our commitment, but the love and energy of everyone who was there with us.\"</p><p>Family heritage also found its place throughout the celebration. With Natalie's family travelling from England, British traditions were woven into the menu through Eton Mess for dessert and a Victoria Sponge-inspired wedding cake, creating familiar moments that made loved ones feel at home.</p><p>Welcome traditions but don't be afraid to thoughtfully reinterpret them to reflect your own story, make them your own and in a way that speaks to your story as a couple and your guests. </p>",
            "colour_style": "dark",
            "button_1_metaobject": "",
