    "content_list_pQJTtf": {
      "type": "content-list",
      "blocks": {
        "image_TcpAha": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "apply_overlay": false,
            "devices": "mobile_desktop",
            "content_position": "underLeft",
            "subheading": "",
            "title": "<p>It's The Quiet Moments You'll Carry Forever</p>",
            "description": "<p>Not every meaningful memory happens in front of your guests. Sometimes, they happen in complete stillness. A quiet morning walk before the celebrations begin. A handwritten note from your soon-to-be spouse, filled with reflections on how far you have come together. A moment to pause, breathe and take in the significance of what the day represents before you step into it.</p><p>Because Helen lived on the hill above the church where she was married, she was able to watch her husband arrive from the balcony before the ceremony began. \"It was such a quiet moment amongst all the excitement. We could see one another from afar before everything began.\"</p><p>For Elsa, one of the most treasured moments happened before the celebrations had even begun. Her bridesmaids surprised her with a beautifully bound book filled with handwritten letters from her closest family and friends to read on the morning of the wedding.</p><p>Whilst not easy to plan for entirely, think of how you can create space for quiet reflection, this often becomes one of the most meaningful additions to your wedding day.</p>",
            "description_mobile": "<p>Not every meaningful memory happens in front of your guests. Sometimes, they happen in complete stillness. A quiet morning walk before the celebrations begin. A handwritten note from your soon-to-be spouse, filled with reflections on how far you have come together. A moment to pause, breathe and take in the significance of what the day represents before you step into it.</p><p>Because Helen lived on the hill above the church where she was married, she was able to watch her husband arrive from the balcony before the ceremony began. \"It was such a quiet moment amongst all the excitement. We could see one another from afar before everything began.\"</p><p>For Elsa, one of the most treasured moments happened before the celebrations had even begun. Her bridesmaids surprised her with a beautifully bound book filled with handwritten letters from her closest family and friends to read on the morning of the wedding.</p><p>Whilst not easy to plan for entirely, think of how you can create space for quiet reflection, this often becomes one of the most meaningful additions to your wedding day.</p>",
            "colour_style": "dark",
