    "content_list_QRht9g": {
      "type": "content-list",
      "blocks": {
        "image_iBGjqn": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "apply_overlay": false,
            "devices": "mobile_desktop",
            "content_position": "underLeft",
            "subheading": "",
            "title": "<p>The Smallest Keepsakes Becoming The Most-Treasured</p>",
            "description": "<p>Many couples spend months thinking about styling, florals and tablescapes, its important to not overlook the personal threads throughout your day that guests remember most.</p><p>Rather than traditional place cards, Shona and her husband placed handwritten letters alongside Polaroids for every guest.</p><p>\"They ranged from funny to heartfelt. Little moments of gratitude and memories we'd shared together. Watching everyone read them and take them home was incredibly special.\"</p><p>For Asha, preserving memories will become an experience that would continue well beyond the celebrations. At their upcoming wedding in Italy, every guest will discover a handwritten letter waiting in their room alongside a disposable camera to capture the week through their own perspective. The photographs and letters will later become a keepsake photo book documenting not only the wedding day, but the shared experience surrounding it. During the reception, they'll also project footage from their earlier civil ceremony so loved ones who couldn't attend could still be part of the celebration.</p><p>These thoughtful ideas are also the simplest - a handwritten note, a disposable camera or a personal letter. Small gestures that become treasured long after the flowers have faded and the tables have been cleared.</p>",
            "description_mobile": "<p>Many couples spend months thinking about styling, florals and tablescapes, its important to not overlook the personal threads throughout your day that guests remember most.</p><p>Rather than traditional place cards, Shona and her husband placed handwritten letters alongside Polaroids for every guest.</p><p>\"They ranged from funny to heartfelt. Little moments of gratitude and memories we'd shared together. Watching everyone read them and take them home was incredibly special.\"</p><p>For Asha, preserving memories will become an experience that would continue well beyond the celebrations. At their upcoming wedding in Italy, every guest will discover a handwritten letter waiting in their room alongside a disposable camera to capture the week through their own perspective. The photographs and letters will later become a keepsake photo book documenting not only the wedding day, but the shared experience surrounding it. During the reception, they'll also project footage from their earlier civil ceremony so loved ones who couldn't attend could still be part of the celebration.</p><p>These thoughtful ideas are also the simplest - a handwritten note, a disposable camera or a personal letter. Small gestures that become treasured long after the flowers have faded and the tables have been cleared.</p>",
            "colour_style": "dark",
