    "content_list_Yh7w4M": {
      "type": "content-list",
      "blocks": {
        "image_mayxyk": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "apply_overlay": false,
            "devices": "mobile_desktop",
            "content_position": "underLeft",
            "subheading": "",
            "title": "<p>A Final Thought...</p>",
            "description": "<p>The celebrations that stay with us are the ones where every detail feels intentional. Where traditions are thoughtfully reimagined, keepsakes become heirlooms, and every creative touch reflects the couple at the heart of it all. Where guests leave feeling not only entertained, but truly connected to your story.</p><p>There is no right way to personalise your wedding day. The most memorable ideas are simply the ones that feel true to you.</p><p>Long after the flowers have faded and the tables have been packed away, these are the moments that remain. Not because they were extravagant, but because they were unmistakably yours.</p>",
            "description_mobile": "<p>The most thoughtful wedding details are often the ones that continue to hold meaning long after the day itself. Whether it's a keepsake your guests take home or something that becomes part of your everyday life together, these small touches allow your celebration to live on.</p><p>For Elsa, guests took home custom matchboxes as a simple keepsake, a small reminder of the celebration designed to find a place in their homes long after the last dance. </p><p>Rather than a traditional guest book, the couple invited guests to sign a framed vinyl record of their first dance song. Today, it hangs in the hallway of their home, transforming a beautiful memory into something they pass each day.</p><p>The most thoughtful wedding favours aren't always the most extravagant. Often, they're the small, personal keepsakes that quietly find a place in your guests' homes, carrying a little piece of your celebration with them.</p>",
            "colour_style": "dark",
